<P>
TITANS COMPLETE SWEEP OF UNLV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton finished its three-game Big West Conference series against 
Nevada Las Vegas with a 3-0 victory Sunday at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 While the Titans didn't pound Las Vegas as in the previous two games, they got 
a lift from Dante Powell, who had a triple and three runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans have swept UNLV in their last nine games. 
</P>
<P>
 Titan pitcher Dan Ricabal (4-0), who went the distance, had nine strikeouts 
and gave up five hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton is alone atop the Big West with a 9-3 conference record (31-8 
overall). UNLV (23-20, 5-7) is second in conference. 
</P>
