<P>
MAN INJURED IN 20-FOOT FALL FROM SKYWAY AT DISNEYLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Disneyland visitor fell 20 feet from a Skyway gondola into a tree at the 
Alice in Wonderland ride Sunday and was hospitalized in stable condition, a 
park spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was a 30-year-old man from Highland, Calif., said Lindsay Schnebly, 
a Disneyland spokesman. The park did not release the man's name. 
</P>
<P>
 The customer was helped from the tree by paramedics and taken to Western 
Medical Center, which did not release any information about him. Schnebly said 
the man was able to talk with rescuers after the 10:25 a.m. incident. 
</P>
<P>
 The gondola was removed from service for investigation. 
