<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH STABBED AT THEME PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old Pasadena boy was stabbed several times and another boy was 
robbed of $53 and his beeper in the parking lot at Six Flags Magic Mountain, 
sheriff's deputies said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The youths were assaulted shortly after 9 p.m. Saturday as they waited for a 
tram to take them to their car, said Sheriff's Deputy Diane Hecht. 
</P>
<P>
 The 17-year-old was stabbed in his shoulder, rib cage and ear and was taken to 
Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital, where he was treated and released Sunday, 
a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The other boy, 16, also from Pasadena, was taken to the same hospital and 
treated for minor injuries and released, Hecht said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have no suspects in the incident and are not releasing the 
victims' names. 
</P>
<P>
 In an unrelated incident at the theme park, a 17-year-old suspected gang 
member was arrested and charged with strong-arm robbery after allegedly 
shoplifting shirts from a souvenir store at the park. 
</P>
<P>
 The juvenile was detained by Magic Mountain security officers around 9 p.m. 
Saturday, after initially resisting, Hecht said. The youth was turned over to 
sheriff's deputies and is being held at San Fernando Juvenile Hall in Sylmar. 
</P>
