<P>
ISRAEL EASES BAN ON PALESTINIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Israel has slightly eased an 11-day ban barring the nearly 2 million 
Palestinians of the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip from entering Israel, a 
government minister said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 "The closure is going to continue," Education Minister Amnon Rubinstein told 
reporters after a weekly Cabinet meeting. However, he added, more than 16,000 
entry permits for humanitarian purposes and more than 4,000 work permits have 
been issued. 
</P>
<P>
 "The situation will be weighed from day to day," he said. 
</P>
