<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIESZ TO SIGN WITH REDSKINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Friesz, a free-agent quarterback who played with the San Diego Chargers 
last year, has agreed on a one-year, $900,000 contract with the Washington 
Redskins, the Daily Press of Newport News reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The signing is scheduled for today, the newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm looking forward to playing in Washington," Friesz said. "The opportunity 
to start is what I like." 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Mark Rypien was waived by the Redskins on Wednesday, and 
free-agent backups Cary Conklin and Rich Gannon are unlikely to be offered 
contracts. 
</P>
<P>
 Friesz suffered a knee injury in 1992 and lost his starting job with the 
Chargers to former Redskin Stan Humphries. 
