<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: WILSON NAMES 4 TO COUNTY FAIR BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson's office has announced its 1994 appointments to the Ventura 
County Fair Board, which helps administer the Ventura County Fairgrounds and 
the annual Ventura County Fair. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura lawyer Dennis Orrock and Ventura resident Diane Starr, deputy director 
of a Van Nuys-based energy conservation company, were reappointed to four-year 
terms. 
</P>
<P>
 The governor appointed as first-term directors Georgia Mahan of Somis and 
Virginia Weber of Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Mahan is vice president of Mahan Inc., a real estate and farming company, and 
Weber is an administrative aide with the Ventura County Early Start Program. 
</P>
<P>
 Appointments do not require legislative confirmation, and directors are not 
paid for their services. 
</P>
<P>
 Other directors serving on the nine-member board are Rob Frost of Santa Paula, 
whose term expires in 1995; Tony Grey of Oxnard, whose term expires in 1997; 
board President Earl McPhail of Santa Paula, whose term expires in 1996; Tom 
Pecht of Oxnard, whose term expires in 1995, and Charles Schwabauer of 
Moorpark, whose term expires in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1994 Ventura County Fair will be held Aug. 17 to 28. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
