<P>
WOMAN ESCAPES ATTACKER AT HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 61-year-old Ojai woman narrowly escaped being raped in her home by fighting 
off a young attacker and running to a neighbor's home, a Ventura County 
Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman suffered minor injuries during the struggle early Saturday morning 
and was treated at Ojai Community Hospital and released, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators believe the assailant may be the same person who sexually 
assaulted a woman in her Meiners Oaks home in early March. The assailant is 
described as 5-foot-10, in his mid-20s with brown hair. 
</P>
<P>
 The department is asking that anyone with information about either incident 
contact Detective Maureen Hookstra or Detective Danny Thompson in the Sheriff's 
Department. SCOTT HADLY 
