<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; SCENIC ROAD MAY GET SHOPPING CENTER 
SIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A plan to post a sign for a shopping center along a scenic Simi Valley roadway 
will be considered today by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved, a sign for the Village Shopping Center would be posted on the 
south side of Madera Road near Wood Ranch. 
</P>
<P>
 Signs along scenic roadways are strictly regulated in the city's General Plan. 
There are no other signs along that stretch of roadway, save a low stone marker 
at the entrance to the Ronald Reagan Presidential Library. 
</P>
<P>
 In considering whether to allow the sign, the council will have to decide 
whether to make an exception or change the restrictions on signs along scenic 
roads. SARA CATANIA 
