EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; PANEL WILL WEIGH REMOVAL OF 5 OAKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A proposal to uproot five oak trees on two acres of overgrown property near 
Haigh Road in Newbury Park to make way for a townhome development is expected 
to meet approval by the Thousand Oaks Planning Commission today. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan includes 13 three- and four-bedroom townhouses. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents of the surrounding neighborhood submitted a letter to the city 
saying they generally supported the project, but objected to placement of a 
proposed recreation area near adjacent homes. 
</P>
<P>
 If the project is approved, architect Frank Montesinos said construction would 
begin in August and take about one year. 
</P>
<P>
 The public hearing on the project is scheduled for 6:30 p.m. at City Hall, 
2400 Willow Lane, Thousand Oaks. MATTHEW MOSK 
