<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESMOND MADE HER TRAGEDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leigh Silverton writes about the "Sunset Boulevard" plot from the color of her 
agenda, not from the plot ("All Things Are Not Equal in 'Sunset,' " April 
11).She calls Norma Desmond a "mature woman" who is struggling with gaining a 
"modicum of respectability" and isn't being "taken seriously into midlife." 
</P>
<P>
 Oh, please! 
</P>
<P>
 Desmond is not a tragic figure of the prejudice against middle-aged women -- 
she is a tragic figure of herself! She never grew and developed herself to face 
a rapidly changing industry. She never developed her personal life to include 
intimates and family. Her myopic narcissism kept her brief experience with 
success the focal point of her universe. 
</P>
<P>
 LAURA C. SCHLESSINGER 
</P>
<P>
 KFI-AM Radio 640 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
